CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 25, 1961, pg. 27, reads: "He'll Fight For Scouts - Wendell Turner of the Daniels Athletic Club (seated) will wing his way toward victory at the Centre Avenue YMCA, Dec. 1, in a feature test with George Tillman. Boy Scouts (left to right) include: Melvin Daniels, Jayfus Scott and Tyrone Mitchell.  Scouts will share in net proceeds.Rip Daniels is the brother of fight trainer Charlie Daniels.
TitMainTitle: Boxer Wendell E. Turner, with Rip Daniels standing behind him, surrounded by Boy Scouts Melvin Daniels, Jayfus Scott, and Tyrone Mitchell, for Boy Scout fundraiser at Centre Avenue YMCA
